  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nSome emojis are either clipped or not well centered inside [Tag components](https://www.figma.com/file/WQZcp6S0EnzxdTL4taoKDv/Design-System-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=180-9685&mode=design&t=o9Dby9tUosgMJqRr-0). The problem appears to exist in both Desktop & Mobile clients.\r\n\r\nI'm flagging this issue here in `status-mobile`, but it doesn't mean the root cause is in the mobile code because it doesn't do any processing on the emoji string provided by status-go. @Francesca-G recently reported a bug with an emoji where it's clipped, but I couldn't reproduce yet, but still, I think both bugs are related.\r\n\r\nZoom in the following screenshot to see that in both clients the car emoji is not vertically centered. \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/46027/7de36b99-d5a5-4ae8-998a-5b50b8e23651\" width=\"800\" />\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nNotice the emoji is clipped.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/46027/413d8b07-cf60-4b8a-bedb-405f69a089db\" width=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n## Resources\r\n\r\n- Figma comment about the clipped tag https://www.figma.com/file/Tf5nfkYvpbnNCo4rKLK7lS?node-id=3271:192285&mode=design#489873879",
